25:15.786 --> 25:17.487
♪ 'Cause you know
we'll make it through ♪

25:17.521 --> 25:19.756
♪ We'll make it through. ♪

25:19.790 --> 25:21.791
(crying)

25:27.631 --> 25:30.300
(sighs)

25:30.334 --> 25:32.702
I guess I can still
saw your heart.

25:32.737 --> 25:34.070
(sniffles)

25:34.105 --> 25:36.005
I loved the song,

25:36.040 --> 25:39.008
but I'm not crying over you.

25:39.043 --> 25:41.411
I'm crying because

25:41.445 --> 25:43.580
until you sang that song,

25:43.614 --> 25:45.882
I had actually
forgotten about it.

25:45.916 --> 25:48.752
In a couple years...

25:48.786 --> 25:50.420
we'll forget all of this.

25:50.454 --> 25:52.822
Well, that's why you gotta
keep holding on to your past.

25:52.857 --> 25:54.524
And not be ashamed of it.

25:54.558 --> 25:56.192
I'd rather look forward.

25:56.227 --> 25:58.261
We all love you for who you are.

25:58.295 --> 26:00.430
And I'm in love with Biff.

26:07.865 --> 26:10.305
(school bell ringing)
All right, everybody!

26:10.330 --> 26:11.630
No more drama.
Time to vote

26:11.665 --> 26:13.532
for either Rachel or Mercedes.

26:13.567 --> 26:14.633
Excuse me, Schuester.

26:14.668 --> 26:16.435
Before we cast
another pointless vote

26:16.469 --> 26:18.671
in a meaningless contest

26:18.705 --> 26:21.607
that has absolutely no practical
ramifications whatsoever,

26:21.641 --> 26:22.808
I would like to say

26:22.842 --> 26:24.602
some words about
my good friend Rachel Berry.

26:26.546 --> 26:29.381
Rachel Berry is the most

26:29.416 --> 26:30.883
horrible human being
on the planet.

26:30.917 --> 26:32.818
- What?
- Can it, troll.

26:32.852 --> 26:34.386
Santana... SANTANA:
You have sold

26:34.421 --> 26:36.255
half the people in this room
down the river

26:36.289 --> 26:37.590
more times than I can count

26:37.624 --> 26:40.192
so that you can get a solo
or the lead in a musical,

26:40.226 --> 26:42.194
and I'm pretty sure
that you don't know the names

26:42.228 --> 26:43.562
of the other half of the people.

26:43.597 --> 26:44.697
That's not true.

26:44.731 --> 26:46.432
All right, what is his name?

26:46.466 --> 26:47.266
Rick.

26:47.300 --> 26:48.381
SANTANA:
Exactly. Thank you.

26:48.401 --> 26:50.235
See, you've all
met Rachel, okay?

26:50.270 --> 26:51.537
But I've... I live with her.

26:51.571 --> 26:54.073
Let me tell you what it's like

26:54.107 --> 26:55.407
to share a bathroom with this

26:55.442 --> 26:57.343
stubby, undergrown
little cretin.

26:57.377 --> 26:59.511
Someone in that apartment

26:59.546 --> 27:00.846
shaves their face

27:00.880 --> 27:02.348
and leaves their stubble
in the sink,

27:02.382 --> 27:04.550
and we all know it ain't
Kurt, so do the math.

27:04.584 --> 27:06.385
That's a lie. SANTANA: You
know what else is a lie?

27:06.419 --> 27:07.920
When you won Prom Queen.

27:07.954 --> 27:09.234
What? SANTANA: Yeah,
that's right.

27:09.255 --> 27:10.556
You didn't win, okay?

27:10.590 --> 27:12.324
Everybody just felt
really bad for you,

27:12.359 --> 27:13.799
and the two people
that you hate most

27:13.827 --> 27:15.060
in this whole world,
Quinn and I,

27:15.095 --> 27:17.062
stuffed the ballot box
so that you would win.

27:17.097 --> 27:19.965
You're so cruel, Santana.

27:20.000 --> 27:21.967
I mean, you're only
doing this to me

27:22.002 --> 27:23.502
because I'm the lead
of <i>Funny Girl</i>

27:23.536 --> 27:25.270
and you're just
the lowly understudy.

27:25.305 --> 27:28.507
You want to make me feel bad
because I'm better than you.

27:28.541 --> 27:30.542
And you're an awful person.

27:31.778 --> 27:33.712
Oh! I feel so much better.
Let's vote.

27:33.747 --> 27:35.414
(school bell ringing)

27:37.000 --> 27:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

27:48.495 --> 27:51.063
Well, that Santana rant
really brought me back.

27:52.666 --> 27:54.199
(crying):
You don't even know

27:54.234 --> 27:55.501
what it's like in New York.

27:55.535 --> 27:57.269
I mean, Santana and I

27:57.303 --> 27:58.604
were close for like a minute,

27:58.638 --> 28:00.305
but now it's like
every single day

28:00.340 --> 28:01.607
is exactly like that.

28:01.641 --> 28:04.443
And now it's like
no matter where I go

28:04.477 --> 28:07.279
or what I do, I'm just back
in high school again.

28:07.313 --> 28:09.314
(sobs)

28:10.350 --> 28:11.316
(exhales)

28:11.351 --> 28:12.484
(sniffs)

28:12.519 --> 28:13.819
You know, every time a producer

28:13.853 --> 28:15.287
or an agent tells me that

28:15.321 --> 28:16.321
I'm not good enough

28:16.356 --> 28:18.490
or that I'm not ready...

28:18.525 --> 28:21.126
God, it's like
Santana is saying it.

28:21.161 --> 28:23.028
Or Puck or Quinn

28:23.063 --> 28:24.630
or anybody that's been here

28:24.664 --> 28:26.665
that's ever made me feel small.

28:27.801 --> 28:29.868
Sometimes it's even you.

28:29.903 --> 28:32.438
I'm one of your
high school ghosts?

28:32.472 --> 28:33.439
(sniffs)

28:33.473 --> 28:35.274
It's not necessarily
a bad thing.

28:35.308 --> 28:37.376
I just use all of that stuff,

28:37.410 --> 28:39.478
and I let it motivate me.

28:39.512 --> 28:41.780
It just makes me sad
that you would think

28:41.815 --> 28:43.282
that I'm one of
your tormentors.

28:43.316 --> 28:45.350
I guess I just...

28:45.385 --> 28:47.186
I don't know, I had this

28:47.220 --> 28:48.987
feeling that it was
always me and you

28:49.022 --> 28:50.456
against everyone else.

28:50.490 --> 28:52.491
You were never like them.

28:53.660 --> 28:55.127
You were just always

28:55.161 --> 28:57.196
the best damn singer
that I've ever heard.

28:58.398 --> 29:00.866
You know, and I want you
to be all big

29:00.900 --> 29:02.701
and rich and famous.

29:02.736 --> 29:04.036
I just want to be richer...

29:04.070 --> 29:05.604
(laughs) and bigger...

29:05.638 --> 29:07.573
and more famous.

29:07.607 --> 29:08.574
(laughs)

29:08.608 --> 29:09.975
Oh, don't you think that

29:10.009 --> 29:12.044
Beyoncé and Barbra
feel that way?

29:12.078 --> 29:14.480
Girl, I don't know. Ask me
when I get my first gold record.

29:14.514 --> 29:16.148
(laughs) Okay?

29:16.182 --> 29:17.916
(laughing) Well, I mean,

29:17.951 --> 29:19.251
I will have won

29:19.285 --> 29:20.686
my first Tony by then, so...
Oh...

29:20.720 --> 29:23.555
Come here.
(laughs)

29:23.590 --> 29:25.824
Oh...

29:25.859 --> 29:28.260
After the unpleasantness
of our last encounter,

29:28.294 --> 29:30.662
I decided to do
some deep background

29:30.697 --> 29:32.865
to investigate your claims,

29:32.899 --> 29:35.667
conducted in an intensive
Wikipedia search

29:35.702 --> 29:38.170
that took all of 25 seconds.

29:38.204 --> 29:40.305
You, April Rhodes,

29:40.340 --> 29:41.707
were the mistress of

29:41.741 --> 29:43.342
local strip-mall magnate
Buddy Leibowitz,

29:43.343 --> 29:46.011
whose wife offered
you $2 million

29:46.045 --> 29:47.646
to keep the affair quiet

29:47.680 --> 29:49.548
after her husband's
untimely demise.

29:49.582 --> 29:51.717
It was that money
that you placed into an annuity

29:51.751 --> 29:54.653
to fund the auditorium
in perpetuity.

29:54.687 --> 29:56.255
That's right.

29:56.289 --> 29:57.589
Well, it didn't last.

29:57.624 --> 30:00.292
In fact, that money
ran out six weeks ago.

30:00.326 --> 30:01.393
How?

30:01.427 --> 30:03.662
Will Schuester's
profligate spending

30:03.696 --> 30:07.232
and his penchant for staging
elaborate private bacchanalia

30:07.267 --> 30:10.536
replete with extravagant
scenery and costumes

30:10.570 --> 30:12.871
not seen since
the reign of Caligula.

30:12.906 --> 30:14.907
I have here
a line-item budget

30:14.941 --> 30:16.809
of the jungle set
you constructed

30:16.843 --> 30:18.177
onstage a few weeks back

30:18.211 --> 30:19.912
so the glee club could perform

30:19.946 --> 30:21.079
a Katy Perry song

30:21.114 --> 30:23.615
literally for just you.

30:23.650 --> 30:25.384
Whoa, whoa, hold-hold on.
Let-let me see that.

30:25.418 --> 30:27.286
I don't know what
the problem is,

30:27.320 --> 30:29.221
but whatever money
the glee club needs,

30:29.255 --> 30:30.355
I'm good for it.

30:30.390 --> 30:31.690
April Rhodes is rich!

30:31.724 --> 30:33.926
No, April Rhodes
is under indictment

30:33.960 --> 30:35.594
from the Securities
and Exchange Commission

30:35.628 --> 30:38.597
and in violation of
her $3 million bail

30:38.631 --> 30:41.099
that forbids her from leaving
the state of New York.

30:41.134 --> 30:42.467
Oh, snap!

30:42.502 --> 30:43.702
Wait, what?

30:43.736 --> 30:45.370
Well, what April may have
neglected to mention

30:45.405 --> 30:47.172
is that her most recent john

30:47.207 --> 30:49.942
was none other than
the disgraced financier

30:49.976 --> 30:51.443
Bernie Madoff.

30:51.477 --> 30:53.312
All of April's assets,

30:53.346 --> 30:54.546
including her private island,

30:54.581 --> 30:55.647
have been frozen.

30:55.682 --> 30:57.416
April, is this true?

30:57.450 --> 30:58.450
Gulp.

30:58.484 --> 30:59.885
Sure sounds true, doesn't it?

30:59.919 --> 31:00.886
I'm sorry, Will.

31:00.920 --> 31:02.454
It does appear that

31:02.488 --> 31:04.890
the glee club is indeed over.

31:04.924 --> 31:05.757
(gasps dramatically)

31:05.792 --> 31:08.527
APRIL:
Will, wait! Wait!

31:08.561 --> 31:09.561
This is yours.
Yes.

31:09.596 --> 31:10.796
Will, wait!
I can explain...

31:10.830 --> 31:12.564
Explain what, April?

31:12.599 --> 31:13.765
That's you're a
pathological liar

31:13.800 --> 31:15.033
whom I never should
have trusted?

31:15.068 --> 31:16.635
Yes, exactly.

31:16.669 --> 31:18.337
You did the worst thing

31:18.371 --> 31:20.672
you possibly could've done.

31:20.707 --> 31:22.140
You gave me hope.

31:25.778 --> 31:28.685
What are you talking
about? A tattoo?

31:28.720 --> 31:30.387
It's not that bad.
I mean, it was...

31:30.421 --> 31:31.742
On your lower back?
Ryan Seacrest?

31:31.756 --> 31:32.889
I could get it removed.

31:32.924 --> 31:34.124
There's not a laser big enough.

31:34.158 --> 31:35.258
It's the size of Texas.

31:35.293 --> 31:36.693
You should've told
me this weeks ago.

31:36.728 --> 31:38.228
We're in the 20th century.
That doesn't make sense.

31:38.262 --> 31:39.496
The 21st, almost.
Is there a problem here?

31:39.530 --> 31:40.731
Puck, go away.
Okay? We're...

31:40.765 --> 31:42.366
Was she always this
big of a liar?

31:42.400 --> 31:43.867
QUINN:
I'm coming clean now.

31:43.901 --> 31:45.302
Doesn't that mean something?

31:45.336 --> 31:46.503
Wh... a baby?

31:46.537 --> 31:48.505
I mean, what happens
if we got married

31:48.539 --> 31:50.273
and this kid shows up
looking for money?

31:50.308 --> 31:51.475
Are you crazy?

31:51.509 --> 31:53.310
Was this the loser
who knocked you up?

31:53.344 --> 31:54.911
Yes, yes. Puck is the father.
Yeah.

31:54.946 --> 31:56.413
I am looking for
acceptance here, okay?

31:56.447 --> 31:57.547
This is how I love.

31:57.582 --> 31:59.116
That may be how you

31:59.150 --> 32:00.283
and your loser friends love,

32:00.318 --> 32:01.418
but where I come from,

32:01.452 --> 32:02.819
you carry your past with you.

32:02.854 --> 32:05.188
You are the worst
kind of hypocrite.

32:05.223 --> 32:06.590
You walk around
like you're some

32:06.624 --> 32:07.691
Snow frickin' White,
but you're really

32:07.725 --> 32:09.059
just a dirty little slutbag.

32:09.093 --> 32:10.894
Ow, ow, ow, ow! You
shouldn't have said that.

32:10.928 --> 32:11.895
Let go of my nose!

32:11.929 --> 32:13.663
Ow, God, let go!
Am I bleeding?

32:13.698 --> 32:14.898
Not yet.

32:14.932 --> 32:16.166
(grunting)

32:16.200 --> 32:17.267
You're hurting him! Stop!

32:17.301 --> 32:18.268
PUCK:
Kind of the point!

32:18.302 --> 32:19.269
QUINN:
Knock it off!

32:19.303 --> 32:20.504
Stop!

32:27.278 --> 32:28.779
Help me get him out of here.

32:28.813 --> 32:29.880
Do you have any idea

32:29.914 --> 32:31.048
how much better you are
than this guy?

32:31.082 --> 32:32.516
Look, you can crawl
into the trash

32:32.550 --> 32:33.683
and help him out,

32:33.718 --> 32:35.352
or you can come be
with your real friends

32:35.386 --> 32:36.987
in the choir room.

32:37.021 --> 32:38.255
I'll be waiting.

32:41.726 --> 32:43.393
(school bell ringing)

32:43.428 --> 32:45.108
WILL: All right, everybody.
It's time to get

32:45.129 --> 32:46.530
this voting nonsense
out of the way

32:46.564 --> 32:49.232
so that we can continue on
with what you all came here for:

32:49.267 --> 32:50.700
the music.

32:50.735 --> 32:53.336
Y'all can use your left hand
for anonymity.

32:53.371 --> 32:54.371
But I'm left-handed.

32:54.405 --> 32:55.939
Then use a foot.
Okay.

32:55.973 --> 32:57.507
♪

33:01.279 --> 33:02.913
Dude, who you putting on?

33:02.947 --> 33:04.081
Well, I'm torn.

33:04.115 --> 33:05.615
One is black and one is Jewish.

33:08.086 --> 33:09.586
Okay, that's everybody.

33:14.158 --> 33:15.659
So, um,

33:15.693 --> 33:18.395
sorry about that
outburst earlier.

33:18.429 --> 33:20.564
Mercedes and I
have been talking.

33:20.598 --> 33:24.034
And we both realize that
asking you guys to vote

33:24.068 --> 33:26.636
for who's more talented is just,
it's completely ridiculous,

33:26.671 --> 33:27.704
unproductive

33:27.738 --> 33:29.906
and narcissistic. I mean,

33:29.941 --> 33:31.475
how could we ask you guys

33:31.509 --> 33:33.777
to choose between two
beautiful queen divas?

33:33.811 --> 33:35.132
Well, funny enough,
they did vote,

33:35.146 --> 33:36.313
and they did choose.

33:36.347 --> 33:38.348
And guess what.

33:38.382 --> 33:40.684
You're both equally talented
in their eyes.

33:40.718 --> 33:42.819
And mine.
(both laugh)

33:42.854 --> 33:44.121
(applause)

33:46.124 --> 33:47.591
Excuse me, excuse me.

33:47.625 --> 33:49.259
I'd like to apologize.

33:49.293 --> 33:51.294
It's not the first time I've
raised someone's hopes

33:51.329 --> 33:54.197
and then left them
on the rocky shores

33:54.232 --> 33:56.266
of disappointment and regret.

33:56.300 --> 33:58.935
Just ask all of my A.A.
sponsors. April?

33:58.970 --> 34:01.404
We just want to spend the rest
of the week singing in peace.

34:01.439 --> 34:03.340
But I did do was use
the last few hours

34:03.374 --> 34:04.674
of my NetJets account

34:04.709 --> 34:06.776
to bring in someone
whose infectious happiness

34:06.811 --> 34:09.446
surely will make the next
few days that much brighter.

34:09.480 --> 34:11.982
Ladies and gentlemen...

34:12.016 --> 34:13.617
(cheering)

34:15.286 --> 34:18.355
<i>Hola, clase.</i>

34:18.389 --> 34:20.357
April, thank you for
buttering the floor for me.

34:20.391 --> 34:22.692
You know I like
to make an entrance.

34:22.726 --> 34:23.693
Wait, I'm-I'm sorry.

34:23.728 --> 34:25.562
How-how do you two
know each other?

34:25.596 --> 34:26.963
Oh, because there's
a whole Facebook page

34:26.998 --> 34:28.364
for people who were
guests of Glee Club.

34:28.399 --> 34:29.498
I'm on it, April...

34:29.534 --> 34:31.333
Blaine's brother, Rachel's mom,

34:31.369 --> 34:32.435
that Mexican guy.

34:32.469 --> 34:33.436
(laughs):
Holly...

34:33.471 --> 34:35.038
This is amazing.

34:35.072 --> 34:36.139
Where have you been?

34:36.174 --> 34:37.741
Oh, I've been everywhere.

34:37.775 --> 34:39.409
I quit being a
substitute teacher

34:39.443 --> 34:41.344
because I couldn't
stand being tied down.

34:41.379 --> 34:43.547
I like teaching a room
full of kids if I know

34:43.581 --> 34:44.781
I'm never gonna see them again,

34:44.815 --> 34:46.516
but then, if you're
any good at it,

34:46.551 --> 34:47.617
they keep asking you back,

34:47.652 --> 34:49.585
which kind of
defeats the purpose.

34:49.620 --> 34:51.487
So, I started my trademark

34:51.522 --> 34:53.723
Holly Holliday Teachin' Pop-Ups.

34:53.757 --> 34:55.257
I just show up at a classroom

34:55.293 --> 34:57.092
unannounced, teach a lesson

34:57.128 --> 34:58.628
and get the hell out of there.

34:58.663 --> 35:00.664
(old-timey voice):
Hello!

35:00.698 --> 35:04.401
I'm William Henry Harrison,
America's worst president.

35:04.435 --> 35:07.537
I exterminated a nation
of Native Americans,

35:07.572 --> 35:08.872
and it got me elected.

35:08.906 --> 35:11.641
But I refused to wear a coat
to my inauguration,

35:11.676 --> 35:13.810
so I caught a cold
and died a month later.

35:13.844 --> 35:15.845
I accomplished nothing!
(footsteps approaching)

35:15.880 --> 35:16.913
WOMAN:
There she is!

35:16.948 --> 35:18.582
She just showed up,
and she took

35:18.616 --> 35:19.816
over my class!

35:19.850 --> 35:21.618
Tippy-canoe!

35:21.652 --> 35:23.687
But when I heard
Glee Club was ending,

35:23.721 --> 35:26.256
I ripped off my Pol Pot uniform,

35:26.290 --> 35:28.625
hopped on that first flight
out of Buenos Aires

35:28.659 --> 35:30.627
and came to pay my respects.

35:30.661 --> 35:31.828
Uh, Holly, you know
that we're singing

35:31.862 --> 35:32.929
our favorite Glee Club songs

35:32.964 --> 35:34.431
we've already sung before.

35:34.465 --> 35:36.099
That's a terrible idea!

35:36.133 --> 35:38.268
Listen, that might be
fine for you nerds,

35:38.302 --> 35:40.470
but when Holly Holliday
is in town,

35:40.504 --> 35:43.173
this hot bitch is not looking
in the rearview mirror;

35:43.207 --> 35:44.874
she's looking forward.

35:44.909 --> 35:45.976
Hit it!

35:46.010 --> 35:47.911
(Pharrell's "Happy" begins)

35:47.945 --> 35:50.714
♪ It might seem crazy
what I'm about to say ♪

35:50.748 --> 35:53.850
